---
description: Require Conductor intent contracts during implementation work
alwaysApply: true
---

Before implementation work:

1. If `.conductor/intent-contract.yaml` is missing, draft one with
   `conductor extract --project . --text "<user ask>"`.
2. Do not treat a draft as approved. Ask the user to review it, then run
   `conductor freeze --project . --approved-by "<name>"`.
3. **One contract per feature branch** — regenerate extract/freeze when scope
   changes; do not reuse a stale contract from another task (e.g. the integration
   contract on `main` is not a template for product work).
4. At the start of a resumed session, run `conductor-resume --project .` and
   use the Session Brief as the authoritative intent context.
5. Before claiming completion or committing, run
   `conductor-check --project . --staged`.
6. If the user intentionally changes scope, record it with
   `conductor-pivot --project . --change "<summary>" --acknowledge`.

Cursor has project rules and AGENTS.md support, but this rule is not a lifecycle
hook. For mechanical enforcement use `conductor hook install --project .`
(or repo-local `.githooks` when the consuming app ships its own hook).
